               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18350202-650-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-650-18350202 t18350202-650-offence-1 t18350202-650-verdict-2"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18350202-650-charge-3" targOrder="Y" targets="def3-650-18350202 t18350202-650-offence-2 t18350202-650-verdict-3"></join>
               <p>650. <persName id="def1-650-18350202" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-650-18350202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-650-18350202" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-650-18350202" type="surname" value="JUSTICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-650-18350202" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN JUSTICE</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-650-18350202" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-650-18350202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-650-18350202" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-650-18350202" type="surname" value="PALMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-650-18350202" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM PALMER</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18350202-650-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350202-650-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350202-650-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18350202-cd-150" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350202-650-offence-1 t18350202-cd-150"></join>4th of February</rs>, at St. Mary, Newington, 26lbs. weight of soap, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 21lbs., weight of candles; the goods of <persName id="t18350202-name-1078" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1078" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1078" type="surname" value="PIKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1078" type="given" value="JABEZ"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350202-650-offence-1 t18350202-name-1078"></join>Jabez Pike</persName>, the master of John Justice; and </rs>
                  <persName id="def3-650-18350202" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def3-650-18350202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-650-18350202" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-650-18350202" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM MILLER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted for<rs id="t18350202-650-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350202-650-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350202-650-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp> felo<lb></lb>niously receiving 12lbs. weight of soap, value 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and 21lbs. weight of candles, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., part of the said goods, well knowing them to be stolen, as aforesaid.—2nd <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, for receiving of an evil disposed person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1080" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1080" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1080" type="surname" value="PIKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1080" type="given" value="JABEZ"></interp>JABEZ PIKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an oil and colourman. Justice was in my employ, as porter—I sent him on errands to deliver goods—Palmer was the servant of a Mr. Holraan, my neighbour—my premises open upon Holman's yard—on the night of the 4th of February, I received information from Holman, and accompanied him to a cart-shed in his yard; and under the cart, in a box, I saw a quantity of soap, which I had every reason to believe was mine, from having a similar description of goods on my premises—Holman went into the loft, and there was a quantity of candles in a canvass bag—I have every reason to believe they were mine, having candles of a similar description on my premises—I got a policeman, and went to Holman's premises again, and in the interval the property had been removed—the candles from the loft, and the soap from the box—I found near the box five bars of soap afterwards in a nose-bag—in consequence of information we went to a shop in Arbour-street, within fifty yards of my premises, and there saw Miller—I told him I had come for the soap and candles which Holman's boy had left a few minutes before—his reply was, "I have no candles"—I said, "It is no use to deny it; we know all about it;" and then he stooped down, opened a drawer, and produced the soap, and after<lb></lb>wards the candles, in a canvass bag—I believe the bag to be the same as I had seen in Holman's loft—I got a policeman, and gave Justice and Pal<lb></lb>mer into custody—I value the candles at 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and the soap at 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—Miller keeps a chandler's shop—Holman is a carter.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I believe you stated to Miller that what you wanted was some soap and candles, which Holman's boy had brought? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—the prisoners were all before the magistrate—Justice and Palmer were detained—I undertook Miller should come next day, and he was let go on that—he has been a neighbour of mine many years—he came according to promise next day—I offered the magistrate to become bail for him—the magistrate said as the Grand Jury were sitting, it was not worth while—I have supplied Miller with goods, but not for months past.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1081" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1081" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1081" type="surname" value="BOOTH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1081" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BOOTH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman N</hi> 99.) I was on duty between nine and ten o'clock at night on the 4th of February, in Newington-causeway—Mr. Holman fetched me to his premises—I went with him and the prosecu<lb></lb>tor,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183502020183"></xptr>
               <p>and saw Palmer—Holman said, "Charles, the policeman wants you concerning some soap and candles"—he said, "Master, I do not know any thing about soap and candles"—he said, "You do, for there is soap and candles deposited on my premises unknown to me, and they have no business there"—I took him into custody—Mr. Holman immediately said there was some soap in a box in the cart-shed, and candles in a bag in the loft—Holman went to the loft, and found the candles were removed—I afterwards went with the prosecutor to the cart-shed, and the soap was also removed—Palmer said he did not know any thing about them—the prosecutor stated that he did know, and, if in case they were not there, he knew where they were, from information he received—I went to Pike's house, and took Justice into custody, and went from there to Miller's—Pike said, "Mr. Miller, I have come for the soap and candles which have been brought here"—Mr. Miller said, "What soap and candles?"—he said, "The soap and candles brought by Holman's boy"—he hesitated a moment, then opened a drawer, and brought out four bars of soap, and then the bag of candles, and laid them on the counter—I took possession of them, and took them to the station-house with Palmer and Justice in my custody—I went back to Miller's house, and fetched him to the station-house—I then went and examined Holman's yard, and found five bars of soap under a cart-shed, behind a large piece of board—Palmer had said, in my presence, that there was more soap in a nose-bag in the cart-shed—I found that—he said he had taken the candles and soap to Miller's shop, and stated to Miller that he should call for them that evening.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1082" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1082" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1082" type="surname" value="FEARON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1082" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES FEARON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter, and live in George-street. I was at the prosecutor's house—in consequence of what he said to me, I remained in the parlour with Justice—I said what a shocking thing it was for a young lad like him, and what a shocking thing it would be for his father and mother, and if he was a lad of mine, it would almost break my heart—he burst into tears, and said, "What will my father and mother say?"—he stated to me that he had taken about thirty-four or thirty-five cakes of soap, and about two dozen candles, from his master.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1083" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1083" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1083" type="surname" value="PIKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1083" type="given" value="JABEZ"></interp>JABEZ PIKE</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I have every reason to believe this is my soap—I have a great deal of it at home—I am more positive of the candles—there are certain candles there which I know—one of them is a candle eight to the pound, a long description of candle, which I know well to be mine—I did not miss any, our stock is too large.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Palmer's Defence.</hi> Justice called me out in the morning, and said he had some soap, if I was of a mind to take it—I went up the yard, just opened the gate, and he gave it into my hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Miller's Defence.</hi> Palmer brought the goods to my house, and asked me to let him leave them till he called for them.</p>
               <p>(Several respectable witnesses gave Miller a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">JUSTICE—
<rs id="t18350202-650-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
